docs.text: play it to the bone , the newest addition to ron shelton's sports - themed repertoire fails in numerous ways .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: like most of shelton's other great films ( bull durham , white men can't jump ) , this dud unsuccessfully attempts to use athleticism as a method of connecting characters and creating interesting subplots .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: shelton's films are not considered sports films , but they do heavily revolve around a specific game to tell a story .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: shelton has been so good in the past at using sports to analyze the structure of society that from his collection of films we are given an examination of different classes and races living in various different regions .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: play it to the bone is unsuccessful because not only is the boxing theme dull , but the side story of the two guys and a girl travelling across the country is even worse .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film has no social message like its predecessors .

docs.text: the relationship between the friends , two failed boxers who must face off against each other in the ring for 50 thousand dollars , is very confusing for a number of reasons .

docs.text: the whole film , since it is primarily a " buddy picture , " depends on the strength of the friendship the two characters have for each other .

docs.text: unfortunately , it is a very weak bond for the reasons listed below .

docs.text: 1 ) we never see how cesar ( antonio banderas ) and vince ( woody harrelson ) meet .

docs.text: the two are so different from each other , that a scene of how this odd friendship developed should have been mandatory .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: 2 ) vince and cesar argue every moment possible on their trip to las vegas .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is not one convincing moment dedicated to seeing the characters laugh together or actually agree on something .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: 3 ) the third character on the trip , grace ( lolita davidovich ) stands in the way .

docs.text: she is in nearly every scene with them , making it impossible to understand the difficulty the two male characters are going to have when they fight each other .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: 4 ) there are two many interfering , irrelevant side stories .

docs.text: vince is convinced that he sees jesus on a regular basis , cesar yells at the sky in spanish when he is angry , and grace tries to sell her inventions to hotel owner robert wagner .

docs.text: these boring tales only hurt the central plot .
